a:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Who Should Choose Which?"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"The ideal user for each platform differs considerably. DeepAI is best suited for API integration, developers, simple generation, prototyping, making it a strong choice if you fall into any of these categories. Imagine AI, meanwhile, shines for mobile art, social media, avatars, quick generation, which means it may be the better pick if your needs align with those use cases.\n\nFounded in 2017, DeepAI describes itself as \"Simple AI image generation API for developers.\" Imagine AI, established in 2022, positions itself as \"Mobile AI art generator with diverse artistic styles.\" Both platforms have been in the market for a similar duration, giving each ample time to refine their offerings and build a loyal user base."}]]}]
b:["$","div",null,{"className":"verdict-box","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Our Verdict"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"After analyzing all the data, **Imagine AI** comes out slightly ahead in this comparison, thanks to higher user ratings (5.0 vs 4.0), availability of a free plan. However, this does not mean DeepAI is a poor choice — far from it. DeepAI excels in its own right, particularly for API integration and developers.\n\nOur recommendation: if you value good mobile experience, go with Imagine AI. If simple api for quick integration matters more to you, DeepAI is the way to go. Either way, both are solid platforms that have earned their place in the market."}]]}]
